contact_name: Eurostat, the statistical office of the European Union
description: The deflated house price index (or real house price index) is the ratio between the house price index (HPI) and the national accounts deflator for private final consumption expenditure (households and non-profit institutions serving households (NPIs) ). This indicator therefore measures inflation in the house market relative to inflation in the final consumption expenditure of households and NPIs. Eurostat HPI captures price changes of all residential properties purchased by households (flats, detached houses, terraced houses, etc.), both new and existing, independently of their final use and their previous owners. Only market prices are considered, self-build dwellings are therefore excluded. The land component is included. The data are expressed as quarterly index (2010=100), annual rate of change and quarterly rate of change.

    <dct:title xml:lang="en">House price index, deflated - quarterly data</dct:title>
    <dct:title xml:lang="fr">Indice des prix des logements, déflaté - données trimestrielles</dct:title>
    <dct:title xml:lang="de">Hauspreisindex, bereinigt - vierteljährliche Daten</dct:title>
    <dct:identifier>tipsho30</dct:identifier>
    <dct:description xml:lang="en">The deflated house price index (or real house price index) is the ratio between the house price index (HPI) and the national accounts deflator for private final consumption expenditure (households and non-profit institutions serving households (NPIs) ). This indicator therefore measures inflation in the house market relative to inflation in the final consumption expenditure of households and NPIs. Eurostat HPI captures price changes of all residential properties purchased by households (flats, detached houses, terraced houses, etc.), both new and existing, independently of their final use and their previous owners. Only market prices are considered, self-build dwellings are therefore excluded. The land component is included. The data are expressed as quarterly index (2010=100), annual rate of change and quarterly rate of change.</dct:description>
    <dct:description xml:lang="fr">L'indice déflaté des prix des logements (ou prix réels des logements) est le ratio entre l'indice des prix des logements (IPL) et le déflateur des dépenses de consommation finale privée [ménages et institutions sans but lucratif au service des ménages (ISBL)]. Par conséquent, cet indicateur mesure l'inflation sur le marché des logements comparée à celle de la consommation finale des ménages et des ISBL. Les données sont exprimées sous forme d'indice trimestriel (2010=100), de taux de variation annuel et de taux de variation trimestriel.</dct:description>
    <dct:description xml:lang="de">Der bereinigte Hauspreisindex (oder Wohnimmobilienindex zu realen Preisen) ist das Verhältnis zwischen dem Hauspreisindex und dem Deflator der Volkswirtschaftlichen Gesamtrechnungen für die privaten Konsumausgaben nach dem Verbrauchskonzept (private Haushalte und private Organisationen ohne Erwerbszweck). Dieser Indikator misst somit die Inflation am Markt für Wohnimmobilien im Verhältnis zur Inflation der Konsumausgaben der privaten Haushalte und privaten Organisationen ohne Erwerbszweck. Die Angaben werden als vierteljährlicher Index (2010 = 100) sowie als jährliche und vierteljährliche Veränderungsrate dargestellt.</dct:description>
